wikipedia_page.main: Paul van der Gucht (2 November 1911 – 15 December 1993) was an English cricketer. He played for Gloucestershire between 1932 and 1933, and later had a long first-class career in India, representing the Europeans in the Bombay Quadrangular from 1935 to 1936 and Bengal in the Ranji Trophy from 1937 to 1947.
